<title>ITALY: Italy's Naples sees May CPI at 0.0 pct mo/mo.</title>
<headline>Italy's Naples sees May CPI at 0.0 pct mo/mo.</headline>
<dateline>NAPLES, Italy 1997-05-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Naples said its May consumer price index stood at 0.0 percent month on month and 2.1 percent year on year.</p>
<p>In April, Naples' inflation rate was 0.3 percent month on month and 2.5 percent year on year.</p>
<p>Naples is one of 11 Italian cities publishing inflation data Tuesday and Wednesday. The city's CPI weighs 6.64 percent on the national index. The 11 sample cities have a combined weighting of 75.66 percent on the total index.</p>
<p>The following is the breakdown of the price changes:</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to April 1997)</p>
<p>					  Month/Month	Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		   0.0    (0.3)     2.1    (2.5)</p>
<p>    Food				0.1    (0.3)     2.0    (2.4)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	 0.0    (0.1)     1.4    (1.7)</p>
<p>    Housing/utility charges     0.0    (0.6)     2.1    (2.0)</p>
<p>    Furniture			-0.1    (0.1)     1.3    (1.6)</p>
<p>    Health services		 0.2    (0.0)     2.8    (2.7)</p>
<p>    Transportation		  0.4    (0.0)     2.9    (3.9)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture  -1.2   (-0.2)     0.9    (2.3)</p>
<p>    Education			 0.0    (0.0)     4.1    (4.1)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	0.1    (0.7)     2.7    (3.5)</p>
<p>    Other goods and services    1.2    (0.5)     3.5    (2.3)</p>
